====Usage notes====
Perfective form is {{m|ja|でした|tr=deshita}}, volitional {{m|ja|でしょう|tr=deshou}}, conjunctive {{m|ja|でして|tr=deshite}}. Other forms are not used.

Replaces {{m|ja|だ|tr=da}} in cases of nouns and adjectives which it is used with, e.g. {{lang|ja|[[犬]]だ}} becomes {{lang|ja|犬です}} and {{lang|ja|[[綺麗]]だ}} becomes {{lang|ja|綺麗です}}. Similarly, {{m|ja|でしょう|tr=deshou}} replaces {{m|ja|だろう|tr=darou}} and {{m|ja|でして|tr=deshite}} replaces {{m|ja|で|tr=de}}.

{{m|ja|です|tr=desu}} attaches as is to adjectives used without {{l|ja|だ|tr=da}}, e.g. {{lang|ja|[[美しい]]}} becomes {{lang|ja|美しいです}} and {{lang|ja|美しかった}} becomes {{lang|ja|美しかったです}}. Forms such as {{lang|ja|美しいでした}} and {{lang|ja|美しいでして}} are nonstandard. For the forms {{m|ja|ない|ないです|tr=nai desu}} and {{m|ja|ない|なかったです|tr=nakatta desu}}, there are synonyms {{m|ja|ありません|tr=arimasen}} and {{m|ja|ありません|ありませんでした|tr=arimasen deshita}}. It can also be used to ask questions; {{l|ja|[[本]][[です]][[か]]}} means "Is this a book?"

This word is phonologically an [[enclitic]], similar to [[particle]]s. It is classified as {{m|ja|助動詞|tr=jodōshi||auxiliary verb}} in traditional Japanese grammar.

